name: xylan 1,4-beta-xylosidase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: Hydrolysis of (1->4)-beta-D-xylans, to remove successive D-xylose residues from the non-reducing termini
comment: Also hydrolyses xylobiose. Some other exoglycosidase activities have been found associated with this enzyme in sheep liver.

pathways.ec00520: Amino sugar and nucleotide sugar metabolism

references.title: Purification and characterization of a broad specificity beta-glucosidase from sheep liver.
The pentosanases of some rumen bacteria.
